1. python 
apt-get install python (version 2.7 by default)

2. pip install shadowsocks

3. ssserver command (details to check ssserver -h)

4. config file for ssserver 

```
{ 
   "server":"my_server_ip", 
   "server_port":25, 
   "local_address": "127.0.0.1", 
   "local_port":1080, 
   "password":"mypassword",
   "timeout":300, 
   "method":"aes-256-cfb", 
   "fast_open": false
}
```

